</LENGTH>
<HEADLINE>
<P>
NIBBLES AND BITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A preliminary estimate indicates that the Laguna Art Museum netted $100,000 
with its 13th annual art auction Saturday, a 20% decline from last year's take. 
However, last year's was seen as abnormally high because part of the proceeds 
were earmarked for artists who lost property in the Laguna Canyon fire. All the 
money raised this year will benefit the museum's education programs. 
</P>
<P>
 Compiled by Ken Williams 
</P>
</TEXT>
