<HEADLINE>
<P>
PLATFORM; ISRAEL'S VICTIMS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By RABBI ELI HECHT, director of Chabad of South Bay and past president of the 
Rabbinical Council of California, reacts to the killing of Israelis by Islamic 
radicals: 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The government of Yitzhak Rabin explains all the murder and violence with a 
new cliche, "Victims of Peace." This is unacceptable. 
</P>
<P>
 By signing a peace treaty with Jordan, Rabin abrogates the hard-earned trust 
he built with Yasser Arafat. He gives the right of caring for the holy places 
to the king of Jordan, poking Arafat in the eye, along with telling him to deal 
with starving Palestinians in Gaza and the West Bank. In the eyes of Hamas, 
Arafat has been diminished. 
</P>
<P>
 Rabin's recent statement placing the blame on all Palestinians is wrong. Hamas 
is the culprit and Arafat cannot control Hamas. The new civil unrest between 
Arabs will travel from Gaza to the West Gank to Golan to Jordan and back to Tel 
Aviv. 
</P>
<P>
 Israel's only way to ensure peace is to immediately stop all peace 
negotiations with all Arab countries. No talks, official or secret, should be 
held until the Arab countries realize that Jewish blood is not cheap. We cannot 
go on burying our dead with the words, "May they rest in peace." 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Opinion 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
