<HEADLINE>
<P>
THE WEEK AHEAD: AMMAN; CLINTON IN MIDEAST 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 President Clinton will arrive in Amman, Jordan, Wednesday to witness the 
signing of the historic peace accord between Israel and Jordan, another step in 
the Mideast peace process that began with the agreement between Israel and the 
Palestine Liberation Organization signed in Washington last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The second step of the ambitious mission will send the American president to 
Damascus, Syria, on Thursday for talks with President Hafez Assad and other 
leaders of Israel's most intransigent enemy.Peace talks between Damascus and 
Jerusalem are stalemated. 
</P>
<P>
 Later that day, the American leader will go to Jerusalem and make an address 
to the Israeli Parliament. He is expected to applaud the Israeli leadership for 
taking risks for peace, and is likely to face vocal opposition from political 
rightists. 
</P>
