<P>
 Alexander I. Solzhenitsyn, the Nobel laureate who was once the scourge of the 
Soviet Union and is now a critic of the Russian government, will address 
Parliament members Friday.8 
</P>
<P>
 The Duma, the lower house of Parliament, invited the author to speak of his 
return after two decades in exile in the United States. Solzhenitsyn landed in 
Vladivostok on May 27 and embarked on a long cross-country trip to Moscow to 
rediscover his homeland. 
</P>
<P>
 He has argued that Russia has lost its spiritual bearings and is taking the 
wrong road away from Communism. 
