COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: WESTMINSTER; FORUM FOR TRUSTEES CANDIDATES TONIGHT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Westminster Council Parent-Teacher Assn. will have a forum tonight for 
candidates running for the Westminster School District Board of Trustees. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum will be at Helen Stacey Intermediate School from 7 to 10 p.m., said 
spokeswoman Candace Bartsch. 
</P>
<P>
 The format will offer candidates' opening and closing remarks. The candidates 
will also respond to written questions from the audience. The forum is a 
nonpartisan event, and no campaign literature will be permitted within the 
auditorium, Bartsch said. 
</P>
<P>
 The Westminster Council PTA represents all the school PTAs districtwide. Helen 
Stacey Intermediate is at 6311 Larchwood Drive in Huntington Beach; most of the 
district's schools are in Westminster. 
</P>
