<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: LOS ANGELES COUNTY; 
COUNTY SETS UP 24-HOUR HOT LINE FOR JOB OPENINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Los Angeles County has established a 24-hour job hot line that features 
information about openings available in all 38 departments. 
</P>
<P>
 "When a person looking for a county job calls this number, they will be 
connected by phone to a menu of employment opportunities," said Supervisor 
Yvonne Brathwaite Burke. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials are hoping the hot line will simplify the job seeker's search. 
</P>
<P>
 "When you're looking for a job with Los Angeles County, you will no longer 
have to commute to the Civic Center or shuttle from department to department to 
stare at the bulletin boards bearing job opportunity notices," said Michael J. 
Henry, the interim director of the Department of Human Resources. 
</P>
<P>
 Although the county has been under a hiring freeze for several years, some 
critical posts are exempt and are routinely filled, Henry said. Most of these 
positions are in the Sheriff's Department and the Department of Health 
Services, each of which has about 300 positions available, Henry said. Overall, 
the county will have about 1,000 job openings over the next 12 months. 
</P>
<P>
 The phone number is (213) 351-LIST. Accessing the menu requires a touch-tone 
phone. 
</P>
</TEXT>
