<HEADLINE>
<P>
UCLA WINS GRANT FOR HOUSING PLAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The federal government has awarded UCLA a $549,000 grant to develop a plan for 
eliminating slumlords and increasing the quality of affordable housing in three 
areas of Los Angeles. 
</P>
<P>
 The money, which will be made available by the Department of Housing and Urban 
Development over two years, also will fund a study of how to increase 
residents' borrowing power in the targeted areas: Pico-Union, Vernon Central 
and the Alameda Corridor. 
</P>
<P>
 The UCLA plan also will address environmental health issues, creation and 
expansion of community credit unions and development of a building materials 
recycling program. 
</P>
