<HEADLINE>
<P>
STATE PANEL ALLOCATES FUNDS FOR FREEWAY PARK-AND-RIDE FACILITY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The California Transportation Commission has set aside $12.2 million to pay 
for a Transit Center park-and-ride facility at the interchange of the Artesia 
and Harbor freeways near Carson. 
</P>
<P>
 The funding includes money for landscaping, a bus terminal, widening of 182nd 
Street, a water treatment center and a 1,000-space park-and-ride lot. 
</P>
<P>
 Construction of the lot is scheduled to begin in March. 
</P>
<P>
 State investigators previously found low levels of hazardous substances and 
methane gas at the site, which was used as a landfill in the 1960s. Caltrans, 
the Regional Water Quality Control Board and the Integrated Waste Management 
Board have jointly monitored the area. 
</P>
<P>
 All three agencies approved Caltrans' remedial action plan to cap the 
landfill, drill wells to ensure that the landfill remains isolated from the 
underground water table and install a gas collection system and water treatment 
center. 
</P>
