COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: TRABUCO CANYON; HUNTINGTON BEACH DRIVER KILLED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Huntington Beach man died Sunday night when the car he was driving failed to 
negotiate a curve on Live Oak Canyon Road, the California Highway Patrol said. 
</P>
<P>
 Brian Joseph Cruzat, 37, who was alone in the car, was driving east about 10 
p.m. when the car went off the road and struck an embankment, said CHP Officer 
Bruce Lian.The car flipped over and rolled back onto the road near Canyon Creek 
Drive, Lian said. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers found a small amount of methamphetamine on Cruzat and were 
investigating the crash as drug-related, Lian said. No other vehicles were 
involved. 
</P>
<P>
 Cruzat, who was wearing a seat belt, was partially ejected from the car and 
suffered head injuries, Lian said. 
</P>
<P>
 He said officers did not know how fast Cruzat was going on the winding road, 
which has a posted 35-m.p.h. speed limit. KEN ELLINGWOOD 
</P>
