<HEADLINE>
<P>
ORANGE COUNTY ALMANAC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The golden orange is graying. 
</P>
<P>
 The number of county residents 65 or older increased by more than a third 
between 1980 and 1990, according to the U.S. Census. 
</P>
<P>
 The county is home to Leisure World retirement communities in Seal Beach and 
Laguna Hills. 
</P>
<P>
 But the growing senior citizen population is being felt around the county. 
Several cities including Irvine have built senior centers and are beefing up 
services for the elderly. Today 
</P>
<P>
 Children are invited to create their own Halloween masks at the Huntington 
Beach Mall. 
</P>
<P>
 Organizers said the fair gives children a chance to be creative and make their 
own trick-or-treat costumes. 
</P>
<P>
 The free event, sponsored by the mall's Kid's Klub, is open to children age 3 
to 12. Mask-making activities will be from 4 to 7 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 Information: (714) 897-2533. Age-group Increases 0-17 years: 12.1% 18-64 
years: 28.4% 64 and older: 37.4% Total: 24.7% 
</P>
