<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS FOCUS: GARDEN GROVE; CANDIDATE INTERVIEWS TO BE TELEVISED TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By BERT ELJERA 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Paragon Cable's Channel 3A will air taped interviews today with City Council 
and mayoral candidates. 
</P>
<P>
 The broadcasts will start with the five candidates for mayor appearing at noon 
and continue with the 12 council candidates featured at 1 p.m. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a little different format," said co-producer and show host Bob Nash."We 
decided to let the viewers get to know the candidates in a series of one-on-one 
interviews. It produced some rather interesting comments, more candid than you 
might get in an open forum." 
</P>
<P>
 The interviews of council candidates will be broadcast again at 4 p.m. today, 
and the mayoral candidate interviews will be rebroadcast at 6:30 p.m. The 
programs will be replayed for the rest of the week and during the first week of 
November, Nash said. 
</P>
<P>
 The program is sponsored by the Garden Grove Cable Television Corp. and 
Paragon Cable and financed in part by a city grant. BERT ELJERA 
</P>
