<P>
 For the nine months, the company said its earnings were $2.36 million, 
compared to a loss of $9.96 million in the first nine months of the year 
before. Revenues were $42.4 million, up 20% from $35.2 million last year. 
</P>
<P>
 The company attributed the nine-month results to improved sales, which 
continued through the third quarter, particularly of switching devices. These 
devices transfer signals for telephone calls, check calling card numbers and do 
other communication functions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
