<HEADLINE>
<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: XIRCOM CLOSES YEAR WITH RECORD PROFIT IN QUARTER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Xircom Inc., a Calabasas-based maker of electronic components, posted record 
earnings in its fiscal fourth quarter. 
</P>
<P>
 In the quarter that ended Sept. 30, the company reported profit of $4.36 
million, up 38% from $3.16 million a year earlier.Revenues rose 58% to $38.9 
million from $24.7 million in the same three-month period a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 For its fiscal year, Xircom posted earnings of $15.9 million on $132 million 
in revenues, compared to a year-earlier profit of $9.65 million on sales of 
$82.2 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Dirk I. Gates, Xircom's chief executive, said the company's growth has been 
fueled by increased demand for the company's network adapters and modems for 
portable personal computers. 
</P>
<P>
 Net income in the latest quarter was reduced by a onetime $339,000 charge 
related to early termination of the lease for the company's corporate office. 
Xircom said it is moving its operations to larger facilities in Thousand Oaks 
in December. 
</P>
</TEXT>
