<P>
REGIONAL ROUNDUP: INDEPENDENT TELEMEDIA TO ACQUIRE 2 COMPANIES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Independent TeleMedia Group, a Sherman Oaks media investment firm, said it has 
signed an agreement to acquire two cable television advertising companies: 
SkyConnect, of Boulder, Colo., and Mediatech Inc., of Chicago. 
</P>
<P>
 The acquisitions are aimed at marketing a new technology that could 
significantly cut the costs of advertising on cable television, said Lew 
Eisaguirre, chief financial officer of Independent TeleMedia. 
</P>
<P>
 SkyConnect has developed a network of systems it calls digital video file 
servers -- a technology capable of distributing advertisements digitally, using 
computers. This could replace the more cumbersome process of duplicating 
videotapes and sending them by mail, Eisaguirre said. 
</P>
<P>
 Under the agreement with SkyConnect, Independent TeleMedia will offer 90% of 
its common stock in exchange for 100% of SkyConnect's outstanding shares, the 
company said. The agreement with Mediatech requires that Independent TeleMedia 
exchange $9.25 million in common stocks and assume $4.5 million of Mediatech's 
debt to acquire the firm. 
</P>
<P>
 The acquisitions are subject to shareholder approval. 
</P>
