REGIONAL ROUNDUP: NEW INDEX TO INCLUDE BENTON OIL AND GAS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Benton Oil and Gas Co., an Oxnard-based petroleum exploration and production 
firm, said it has been chosen for inclusion in the S&P SmallCap 600, a new 
stock index compiled by Standard & Poor's to follow the stock performance of 
600 small-capitalization companies. 
</P>
<P>
 Alex E. Benton, chief executive of the company, said inclusion in the new 
index should bring the company "increased visibility, wider coverage by 
securities analysts and increased liquidity in its stock, as institutional 
investors create investment portfolios which mirror the index." 
</P>
<P>
 The index will be disseminated by Standard & Poor's starting Oct. 31, Benton 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 The median market capitalization of the 600 stocks is about $267 million. 
Benton said its current market capitalization is about $190 million. 
</P>
<P>
 Benton has domestic operations in the Gulf Coast region of Louisiana, and 
international operations in Venezuela and Siberia. 
