<P>
REGIONAL EARNINGS: 3RD-QUARTER EARNINGS DIP 4% AT LOCKHEED 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Lockheed Corp., the Calabasas defense giant, reported that its third-quarter 
earnings slipped 4% to $112 million from $117 million a year earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 However, its 1993 third-quarter profit included a onetime after-tax gain of $9 
million. 
</P>
<P>
 Lockheed's sales in the three months ended Sept. 25 were $3.17 billion, down 
9% from $3.48 billion in sales a year before. 
</P>
<P>
 For the recent nine-month period, Lockheed had net income of $308 million, a 
7% gain from $287 million in earnings in the comparable period of 1993. Its 
nine-month sales were nearly flat at $9.29 billion, compared to $9.33 billion. 
</P>
<P>
 Lockheed's pending merger with Martin Marrietta Corp., which would create the 
world's largest defense concern, is expected to be completed early next year. 
</P>
