attributed its improved financial results to a broadened customer base and 
expansion into communication markets, including fiber-optic transmissions. 
</P>
<P>
 The company also said it has reached a tentative settlement of a class-action 
lawsuit filed against the company by two shareholders in 1992. The suit alleges 
Vitesse violated securities laws by making misleading statements in its 
prospectus in 1991. 
</P>
<P>
 Vitesse said it has agreed to pay $1.4 million to the plaintiffs, of which 
about $975,000 will be covered by the company's insurance carrier. Earnings in 
the latest quarter were hampered by a one-time $425,000 charge related to the 
settlement of the suit. 
</P>
