<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY: AEROSPACE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 FTC Makes Second Inquiry on Lockheed-Martin Merger: The Federal Trade 
Commission has asked for further information from Lockheed Corp. and Martin 
Marietta Corp. about their $10-billion merger plan.Lockheed said a second 
inquiry, extending the review period, was to be expected with such a complex 
proposal. The agency will decide whether the merger would violate antitrust 
laws. It can ask for information only twice and must respond within 20 days of 
receiving supplemental information. Lockheed said it hopes to win approval in 
time for the two aerospace companies to be combined during the first quarter of 
1995. 
</P>
