<P>
BRIEFLY: ENERGY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Times Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mobil May Cut 15,000 Support Jobs Mobil Corp. announced plans to eliminate up 
to that many staff positions worldwide in an effort to eliminate "hundreds of 
millions of dollars" in overhead costs.Mobil currently employs 60,000. The cuts 
could involve as much as 40% of the support staff at Mobil headquarters in 
Fairfax, Va. Support staff jobs range from clerical workers and computer 
programmers to lawyers and accountants. In many cases, the cuts will involve 
consolidating overlapping functions or eliminating operations by contracting 
out the work. Staff support services currently account for 25% of Mobil's 
controllable cash expenses. In recent years, Mobil has eliminated 17,000 jobs 
worldwide at an estimated annual savings of $700 million. 
</P>
