<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VALLEY FOCUS: VAN NUYS; SCIENTIST TO SPEAK AT GANG PEACE SUMMIT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 To bring together the community on issues of gang violence and to celebrate a 
yearlong gang truce in the San Fernando Valley, a peace summit is scheduled 
Saturday at the Church on the Way in Van Nuys.  
</P>
<P>
 It is expected to draw a crowd of more than 3,000 and will include speakers 
such as Los Angeles City Councilman Richard Alarcon, actor John Ratzenberger 
(Cliff Clavin of "Cheers") and scientist Jane Goodall. 
</P>
<P>
 Goodall will help plant a tree at the church to commemorate the occasion, 
according to Richard Patlan of Cities in Schools, a sponsor of the event. 
</P>
<P>
 A rap song and a video presentation about the truce negotiation process also 
are on the day's agenda. 
</P>
<P>
 Since the truce, gang-related homicides have decreased by 99%, according to a 
release on the summit. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
