<TEXT>
<P>
 Market trends: Microsoft Corp. was the volume leader in Monday's 
trading.Gaylord Entertainment Co. announced a third-quarter profit of $7.7 
million on sales of $175.7 million, compared to a year-ago profit of $18.6 
million on sales of $192.6 million. Income per share from continuing operations 
increased 16.7%, to 21 cents from 18 cents, on an increase in revenue of 9.6%. 
Gaylord Entertainment owns Opryland USA, which consists of the "Grand Ole 
Opry," Opryland Park and the Opryland Hotel. 
