<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFCASE: TOURISM AND TRAVEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
Compiled by Chris Woodyard / Times staff writer 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hotels Try Discounts: Major local hotels are discounting rooms to leisure 
travelers for fall, but using different gimmicks to do it. 
</P>
<P>
 Marriott is offering weekend packages through Dec. 31 as low as $69 a night, 
including breakfast for two, at 14 Southland hotels including six in Orange 
County. 
</P>
<P>
 Guests who charge their stay with a Visa card can earn credits that entitle 
them to $20 off on a two-night stay, or $40 on a three-night stay. Or the 
credits can be banked for use at other vacation destinations, from Holland 
America cruises to American Airlines vacation packages. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anaheim Hilton, by contrast, is offering its own weekend deal at $89 a 
night, which also includes breakfast for two. The hook: romance. 
</P>
<P>
 "Hilton's national Romance Survey results show that couples believe going away 
together for a weekend is one of the best ways to keep romance alive," said 
Glenn Hale, general manager. And he couldn't help but plug the place across the 
street. 
</P>
<P>
 "Disneyland is especially nice this time of year because the park has a less 
crowded, leisurely feel about it," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
