<P>
O.C. BRIEFLY: HTP ANNOUNCES CHANGER SYSTEM HOLDING 120 CDS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 HTP International said Monday that it has unveiled a 120-compact disc changer 
system.A 90-disc expansion system will be available by January, 1995. 
</P>
<P>
 Chairman Paul Safronchik said his company's new CD changer sets a standard in 
the industry. Currently, several competitors have components that allow 
consumers to store and choose as many as 100 CD titles. 
</P>
<P>
 Additionally, the system recognizes the name of the artist, title of the CD, 
and song titles without requiring the owner to input that information for each 
CD. 
</P>
<P>
 During a limited introduction phase, the changer will sell for $1,000 to 
$2,000. Safronchik said the price will drop to well below $1,000 once it is 
available in consumer electronics outlets. 
</P>
