<P>
ORANGE COUNTY EARNINGS: BECKMAN INSTRUMENTS REPORTS SLIGHT QUARTERLY DIP IN 
PROFITS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Beckman Instruments Inc., the Fullerton-based manufacturer of automated 
systems and supplies for laboratories, had profit of $11.3 million, or 40 cents 
a share, for the third quarter, down 2% from the $11.5 million, or 42 cents a 
share, recorded for the 1993 third quarter.The company said special charges in 
the most recent third quarter totaled $4.8 million, or 11 cents a share, for 
the ongoing implementation of the company's reorganization plan. Sales rose 
slightly to $217.8 million from $215.6 million. Nine-month profit was $29 
million, or $1.03 a share, compared with $29.4 million, or $1.06 a share, for 
the corresponding three quarters last year. Sales were down slightly, to $638.6 
million from $639.1 million. 
</P>
