<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: SIMI VALLEY; SUPERVISOR HOPEFULS TO FACE OFF IN 
DEBATES 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Candidates for two open seats on the Ventura County Board of Supervisors will 
participate in public debates today and Wednesday in Simi Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Simi Valley Councilwoman Judy Mikels and Moorpark Councilman Scott Montgomery 
will take part in a question-and-answer forum tonight at 7 p.m. at the Pacific 
Beverage Co., 51 W. Easy St. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum is sponsored by the Simi Valley Republican Women's Club Federated. 
</P>
<P>
 The two candidates are competing for the seat being vacated by Supervisor 
Vicky Howard, whose 4th Supervisorial District includes Simi Valley, Moorpark 
and the Santa Rosa Valley. 
</P>
<P>
 Mikels and Montgomery will also join candidates vying for the 2nd 
Supervisorial District seat in a debate scheduled Wednesday at the Ronald 
Reagan Presidential Library, 40 Presidential Drive. 
</P>
<P>
 The forum at 7 p.m. is sponsored by the Ventura County chapter of the League 
of Women Voters. 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks Councilman Frank Schillo and attorney Trudi Loh are competing 
for the seat being vacated by Supervisor Maria VanderKolk. 
</P>
<P>
 VanderKolk's 2nd Supervisorial District includes most of the Conejo Valley and 
Port Hueneme. CARLOS V. LOZANO 
</P>
</TEXT>
