WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: VENTURA; MOTORIST ARRESTED IN HIT-RUN ACCIDENT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 26-year-old Oxnard man, whose license is suspended because of a 
drunk-driving conviction, was being held in Ventura County Jail on Monday after 
allegedly slamming into a pickup truck in east Ventura and injuring the driver, 
authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police arrested Victor Manuel Manrique about 11 p.m. Sunday, after spotting 
his car in El Rio. 
</P>
<P>
 Officers found several empty containers of alcoholic beverages inside 
Manrique's car, police said. He was booked into jail on suspicion of felony 
drunk driving and hit-and-run, and was being held in lieu of $5,000 bail. 
</P>
<P>
 According to police, Manrique plowed into the rear of a truck driven by Ruben 
Gaeta, 35, of Santa Paula while Gaeta was stopped at a red light on Wells Road 
in east Ventura. Gaeta suffered minor injuries in the accident, which occurred 
just before 9 p.m. Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
 Manrique hesitated, then sped away from the scene, according to a witness who 
scribbled down the suspect's license plate and a description of the vehicle. 
</P>
<P>
 After police traced the vehicle registration to El Rio and arrested Manrique, 
the suspect admitted to being involved in a second hit-and-run accident earlier 
Sunday in Santa Paula.  
</P>
<P>
 Manrique is scheduled to be arraigned in Ventura County Municipal Court on 
Wednesday. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
