<HEADLINE>
<P>
PROBST LANDSCAPING 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Your recent articles made it sound like the Thousand Oaks City Council 
shamefully abandoned all of its principles when it recently approved the appeal 
of Mr. and Mrs. Charles Probst to landscape their hillside on Westlake 
Boulevard. 
</P>
<P>
 What the articles did not make clear was that the Planning Commission's own 
staff approved the project, that the homeowners association gave its blessing 
to the landscaping (but not the related storage facility), that the Probst's 
property is not contiguous to any existing dedicated open space (and is located 
amid other fully landscaped, residential properties) and that the proposed 
park-like project is fully supported by the great majority of the area's 
residents. 
</P>
<P>
 The City Council is to be commended for its wise decision and Westlake 
Village/Thousand Oaks will be even more visually attractive as a consequence. 
</P>
<P>
 RALPH BLOCK 
</P>
<P>
 Thousand Oaks 
</P>
</TEXT>
